ext","text":"scoped reducer receives a child action when its state is set to an unrelated case, it will"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"not be able to process the action, which is considered an application logic error and will","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"emit runtime warnings."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This can happen if another reducer in the parent domain changes the child state to an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"unrelated case when it handles the action ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"before"}]},{"type":"text","text":" the scoped reducer runs. For example, a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parent may receive a dismissal action from the child domain:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Reduce { state, action in","  switch action {","  case .loggedIn(.quitButtonTapped):","    state = .loggedOut(LoggedOut.State())","  \/\/ ...","  }","}","Scope(state: \\.loggedIn, action: \\.loggedIn) {","  LoggedIn()  \/\/ ⚠️ Logged-in domain can't handle `quitButtonTapped`","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the parent domain contains additional logic for switching between cases of child state,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"prefer ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/ifCaseLet(_:action:then:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-7sg8d","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", which better ensures that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"child logic runs ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"before"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" any parent logic can replace child state:"}]},{"code":["Reduce { state, action in","  switch action {","  case .loggedIn(.quitButtonTapped):","    state = .loggedOut(LoggedOut.State())","  \/\/ ...","  }","}"